The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 Brazilian striker Marcos Pereira on Friday joined the Mohun Bagan club. The veteran, who reached the city in the morning wasted little time and joined the clubs practice in the evening. Its not an unknown environment. I am well acquainted with the football frenzy in this city. I know there will be pressure to perform But with Barreto and Bhaichung in the lineup, I hope itll be quite an interesting I-league, Marcos said. Mohun Bagan officials though failed to confirm when the Brazilian would officially sign for the club. Meanwhile, East Bengals Alvtio DCunha will be out of action for a couple of days after injuring his hamstring at practice.          
	 The B.M. Chattaraj Memorial Table Tennis Championship will be held at the Rabindra Sarobar Stadium from Saturday. The four-day meet will get over on Tuesday.           
	Table Tennis: B.M. Chattaraj meet at Rabindra Sarobar Stadium from 10am      
	Tennis: Calcutta hard court meet at South Club from 1pm                                                                                                                                                                     
